# PIS Labs — Comprehensive Technical & UX Audit

**Auditor Roles:** Principal Software Architect · Lead UI/UX Engineer · Security/Compliance Auditor
**Date:** April 11, 2026
**Scope:** Full codebase review across 5 pillars

---

## Executive Summary

The PIS Labs codebase is **above average for a solo-founder MVP** — the design system is coherent, the monorepo structure is clean, and the security posture of the `/api/subscribe` route is thoughtful. However, this audit surfaces **12 critical findings** and **9 moderate findings** that must be addressed before a production launch to a B2B audience. The most severe issues cluster around **architecture anti-patterns with `next/dynamic`**, a **duplicate `.env.local` that leaks secrets**, and **missing SEO infrastructure for the `/research/[slug]` pages**.

---

## Pillar 1: Architecture & Next.js Best Practices

### Grade: C+

> [!CAUTION]
> ### CRITICAL: `next/dynamic` on an Async Server Component Defeats the Purpose
> **Files:** [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/USER/Downloads/pis-labs/apps/web/src/app/page.tsx), [Ventures.tsx](file:///c:/Users/USER/Downloads/pis-labs/apps/web/src/components/Ventures.tsx)
>
> `Ventures` is an **async Server Component** (it uses `await` to fetch data). Wrapping it in `next/dynamic` forces it to render on the **client**, which:
> 1. **Breaks server-side data fetching entirely** — `process.env.GOOGLE_SHEETS_API_URL` is `undefined` on the client.
> 2. **Eliminates the ISR caching** (`next: { revalidate: 60 }`) you carefully configured.
> 3. **Adds a loading spinner** for content that should be pre-rendered HTML.
>
> **Fix:** Remove `next/dynamic` from `Ventures`. Import it statically. It's a Server Component — Next.js will stream it automatically. The same applies to `TheModel` and `FounderPhilosophy`, which are also pure Server Components with zero client-side logic.

| Component | `'use client'`? | Has client logic? | `next/dynamic`? | Verdict |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `Navbar` | ✅ Yes | ✅ `useState`, `useEffect`, `useScroll` | No | ✅ Correct |
| `Hero` | ✅ Yes | ✅ Uses `ToastButton` (client context) | No | ✅ Correct |
| `TheModel` | ❌ No | ❌ None | ⚠️ Yes | ❌ **Remove dynamic** |
| `Ventures` | ❌ No | ❌ None (async server fetch) | ⚠️ Yes | ❌ **Remove dynamic** |
| `FounderPhilosophy` | ❌ No | ❌ None | ⚠️ Yes | ❌ **Remove dynamic** |
| `CTA` | ✅ Yes | ✅ `useState`, form logic | ⚠️ Yes | ⚠️ Acceptable, but adds spinner |
| `Footer` | ❌ No | ❌ None | No | ✅ Correct |
| `BackgroundEffects` | ❌ No | ❌ None | No | ✅ Correct |
| `DisableDevTools` | ✅ Yes | ✅ `useEffect` | No | ✅ Correct |
| `ThemeProvider` | ✅ Yes | ✅ Context provider | No | ✅ Correct |
| `ToastProvider` | ✅ Yes | ✅ Context + state | No | ✅ Correct |
| `ToastButton` | ✅ Yes | ✅ Uses toast context | No | ✅ Correct |
| `ThemeToggle` | ✅ Yes | ✅ `useState`, `useTheme` | No | ✅ Correct |

### Finding: Duplicate `.env.local` Files
> [!WARNING]
> **Root `.env.local`** still contains `NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_SHEETS_API_URL` (the old, client-exposed name).
> **`apps/web/.env.local`** correctly uses `GOOGLE_SHEETS_API_URL` (server-only).
>
> The root file is **dead weight** and a potential source of confusion. Next.js in the monorepo only reads from `apps/web/.env.local` when the workspace root is `apps/web`. The root `.env.local` serves no purpose and should be **deleted** to avoid accidental deployment with the wrong variable name.

### Finding: Missing `next-themes` in Web Package
`next-themes` is installed at the **root** `package.json` but not in `apps/web/package.json`. This works due to npm workspace hoisting but is an anti-pattern — if you ever eject the web app into its own deployment, it will break. Move `next-themes` to `apps/web/package.json` under `dependencies`.

### Finding: `dotenv` is Unnecessary
`dotenv` is listed as a root dependency. Next.js handles `.env.local` natively. This package serves no purpose and should be removed.

### Finding: Redundant `packages/*` Workspace
The root `package.json` declares `"packages/*"` as a workspace, but no `packages/` directory exists. This is harmless but untidy — remove it or create the directory when you need shared packages.

