## Pillar 2: UI/UX, Responsiveness & Accessibility

### Grade: B+

### ✅ What's Working Well
- **Mobile-first Tailwind usage** is consistent. No hardcoded pixel widths that would break layouts (the `w-[600px]` in `Hero.tsx` line 12 is on an **absolutely positioned blur element**, not a layout element — safe).
- **Invisible scrollbar** implementation in `globals.css` is thorough (covers WebKit, Firefox, IE/Edge).
- **Toast system** is well-implemented with spring physics and glassmorphism.
- **Collapsible Navbar** correctly uses `lg:hidden` breakpoint, covering both mobile and tablet.
- **`overflow-x-hidden`** on the `page.tsx` wrapper prevents horizontal scroll from background effects.

### Finding: BackgroundEffects Symbols at `left: '90%'` Risk Overflow
> [!WARNING]
> Symbols positioned at `left: '90%'` or `left: '85%'` with `text-xl` size classes could **clip or cause horizontal scroll** on very narrow viewports (< 360px). The parent `div` has `overflow-hidden`, which mitigates this, but the symbols will be **invisible** on those viewports — wasted rendering cycles.
>
> **Recommendation:** Filter symbols to use narrower horizontal ranges on mobile, or cap `left` values at `80%`.

### Finding: Color Contrast Issues in Dark Mode
| Element | Foreground | Background | Approx. Ratio | WCAG AA (4.5:1)? |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Body text (`text-zinc-400` on `bg-black`) | `#a1a1aa` | `#000000` | **5.3:1** | ✅ Pass |
| Muted text (`text-zinc-500` on `bg-black`) | `#71717a` | `#000000` | **3.6:1** | ❌ **Fail** |
| Card subtitle (`text-zinc-600` on `bg-[#1C1C1E]`) | `#52525b` | `#1C1C1E` | **2.4:1** | ❌ **Fail** |
| Toast dot (`bg-zinc-500`) | Decorative | — | N/A | N/A |

**Impact:** `text-zinc-500` and `text-zinc-600` on dark backgrounds fail WCAG AA. This affects labels like "Prefer real-time updates?" in CTA, tech stack labels in Ventures, and the subtitle text in TheModel. Recommend elevating to `text-zinc-400` minimum for all readable text in dark mode.

### Finding: Missing `aria-label` on Social Links
All social icon links in the Footer render icons without text content. Screen readers will announce them as empty links. Each should have `aria-label="X (Twitter)"`, `aria-label="LinkedIn"`, etc.

### Finding: No `<h1>` on Terms/Privacy Pages
Both legal pages use `<h1>` correctly. ✅ Verified.

### Finding: `DisableDevTools` Blocks Right-Click
> [!IMPORTANT]
> Preventing right-click (`contextmenu`) and keyboard shortcuts (F12, Ctrl+U) **does not provide real security** — anyone can disable JavaScript. However, it **actively degrades UX** for legitimate users:
> - Users cannot right-click to open links in new tabs.
> - Users cannot right-click to copy text.
> - Developers debugging production issues are blocked.
>
> **Recommendation:** Remove this component entirely, or at minimum, only ship it in production builds with a feature flag. It provides **zero security value** and maximum UX friction.

