## Pillar 5: SEO & Conversion Funnel

### Grade: C+

### ✅ What's Working Well
- **Root layout metadata** is comprehensive (OG tags, Twitter cards, robots directives). ✅
- **Semantic HTML** is generally good (`<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<footer>`). ✅
- **Single `<h1>` per page** is maintained across all pages. ✅

### Finding: `/research/[slug]` Pages Have No Dynamic Metadata
> [!CAUTION]
> The research case study pages (`/research/credturn`) do **not** export a `generateMetadata` function. They inherit the **global** metadata from `layout.tsx`, meaning:
> - Sharing `/research/credturn` on LinkedIn shows "PIS Labs | Applied AI Venture Studio" instead of "System Architecture: CredTurn."
> - Google indexes these pages with the **wrong title and description**.
>
> **Fix:** Add `generateMetadata` to `[slug]/page.tsx`:
> ```typescript
> export async function generateMetadata({ params }: { params: Promise<{ slug: string }> }) {
>   const { slug } = await params;
>   const project = venturesData.find((v) => v.id === slug);
>   if (!project) return {};
>   return {
>     title: `${project.title} — Case Study | PIS Labs`,
>     description: project.description,
>     openGraph: {
>       title: `${project.title} — Applied AI Case Study`,
>       description: project.description,
>     },
>   };
> }
> ```

### Finding: Terms & Privacy Pages Have No Metadata
Both `/terms` and `/privacy` pages lack exported `metadata` objects. They will show the global "PIS Labs | Applied AI Venture Studio" title in browser tabs, which is not ideal for legal compliance (users should clearly see "Terms of Service" in the tab title).

### Finding: Research Page Design Deviates from Design System
> [!NOTE]
> The `/research/[slug]` page uses a **completely different aesthetic** from the rest of the site:
> - `bg-zinc-950` instead of the system's `bg-white dark:bg-black`.
> - Sharp corners (`rounded-lg`, `rounded-md`) instead of `rounded-3xl`.
> - No dark mode toggle support — it's hardcoded dark.
> - Different button styles (squared, no glassmorphism).
>
> This creates a jarring visual disconnect when navigating from the main site to a case study. Recommendation: Align the research page to the established design tokens.

### Finding: "View All Projects" Button is a Dead Link
The [Ventures.tsx](file:///c:/Users/USER/Downloads/pis-labs/apps/web/src/components/Ventures.tsx) "View All Projects" button (line 69) is a plain `<button>` with no `onClick` handler and no `ToastButton` wrapper. It's a **dead click** — exactly the UX pattern you asked me to eliminate with the toast system.

### Finding: "Book Now" → Calendly is an External Redirect
The conversion funnel from "Book Now" to Calendly works, but it's an **external redirect** that leaves your site. Consider embedding the Calendly widget inline (using `@calendly/react` or an `<iframe>`) to keep users on-domain and reduce drop-off.

### Finding: No `sitemap.xml` or `robots.txt`
Next.js App Router supports `sitemap.ts` and `robots.ts` as route handlers. Neither exists. For a B2B site targeting search visibility, these are essential.

